ref=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Rare mobs and decency...</span><hr size=1> I was in Skyfire when this incident happened.  Guildie asked me to come and help so I did.  When I first came into the zone, I thought everyone there was working together to kill Rage for one person.  Apparently I was wrong.<br>
<br>
I have not idea what was said between the leaderships of the two parties.  Just from my observation, AS did nothing wrong.  I have no idea who got their first, but they are set up and ready before the other party.  I was in the raid chat, and it did not seem that the group was ready.<br>
<br>
I read from other post that so and so should have got it because they had to work harder.  That does not make any sense whatsoever.  Both players worked to get their epic completed.  Just because one person had an easier time in obtaining the pieces, doesn't make it less worthy.  Welcome to he difference between the guild raids and open raids.  <br>
<br>
People join guilds for this very thing.  The guild will always win out when it is time to mobilize and kill something.  If you wanted to makesure you got the mob when it spawned, then why not make a chat, and everyone who can help be on it when they are on.  When said mob spawns, those people will drop whatever they are doing and go kill it.  Do you think that each individual open raider will drop their exp group, raid with their guild, etc. in order to kill said mob?  I hardly doubt it.  Guess what?  The guild will...<br>
<br>
It would be nice if you could have come out with an agreement, but both parties needed the same piece.  Things like these will happen.  Deal with it.  You will get your epic eventually.<br>
